text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia octonervia is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Great Southern and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.1 to 0.5 metres (0 to 2 ft). It blooms from August to November and produces cream-yellow flowers.
